   <note type="biographical/historical" displayLabel="Biographical Note">General O. B. Johnson served as a pilot in the U.S. Army Air Corps in Europe during World War II. He supervised the development of advanced fighter aircraft and their implementation during the Korean War. He later commanded the Washington Area Air Defense Sector, the 14th Aero Space Force, and the 313th Air Division. After retiring from the Air Force in 1973, Johnson served in several positions in the Shreveport city government and as undersecretary of public safety under the Treen administration.</note>
